    HomeScreenActivity

    Home
    Discoveries
    Goals
    Discoveries
    When you open the app, you will be taken to the Discoveries screen. Here, you can select various strength exercises and a walking plan to add to your goals. You can choose from the preset walking plans or set a custom daily step goal.

    // Tutorial
    Set strength exercise goals
    If you select a strength exercise, the app will show you options to either manually set your goal or have the app automatically set your goal based on the details you entered.

    Set group goals
    You can also set a goal for any of the groups that you have created and are an admin of.

    Use preset walking plans
    If you select one of the preset walking plans, the daily step goal will start out at day one, then increase to the next day if you meet that goal.

    Set a custom walking plan
    If you select your custom walking plan, you can select your daily step goal that will not change.

    Goals
    To view all the goals you have set, go to the Goals screen. This screen displays all the goals you have set, including your walking plan. It also shows any goals of groups that you are a member of.

    Log activity for an exercise
    To log activity for one of the exercises, click on it on the Goals screen.

    Groups
    The Groups screen displays all the groups you are a member of.

    Enter group page
    To enter a group page, click on the group you want to view. Each group\'s page displays the goals and members of the group.

    Activities
    To view all the activities you have done in the past, go to the Activities screen.



